temp.fibHeap.stixar.graph
Interface Node

All Superinterfaces:
Attributable
All Known Implementing Classes:
BasicNode, BasicUNode
public interface Node
extends Attributable

A very basic node interface. This interface is the minimal node interface. Programmers may implement this and the corresponding Edge interfaces with a minimum of effort and then benefit from all the supplied read-only graph algorithms.

out

Edge out()
Produce an outgoing edge in the list of outgoing edges, if there is one.

Outgoing for a node u means all edges of the form (u,v) for directed graphs, and means all adjacent edges for undirected graphs.

Returns:
the first in the list of outgoing edges or null if there is no such edge.
